Prerequisites
-------------
webserver (Apache, Nginx) with PHP

Ubuntu / Debian : 
    with Apache : apt-get install apache2 php5 libapache2-mod-php5
    with Nginx : apt-get install nginx php5-fpm

Windows
    You can use Xammp to install Apache and PHP
    

Tested under
- Ubuntu and Windows with Chrome 37+ and Firefox 31+
- Ipad 2 and Iphone 4s on IOs 7
- Android 4.1 on tablet 
    
    
Configuration
-------------

Add the sources in a folder called RocCTC in your webserver root folder
Edit RocCTC.xml to configure your panels (cf doc/RocCTC.xml-example for more detail)

If Rocrail server is not on the same server as your sebserver, edit RocCS.php to change IP and port accordingly

Start RocCTC by typing in your web browser http://localhost/RocCTC

Theming
-------
You can customize the theme by modifying the following files : 
- RocCTC.tpl : Page template
- RocCTC.css : stylesheet
- img/switch-left.png
- img/switch-right.png

Tips
----
With Android and IOs, you can add a shortcut to the home screen and the app will act as a real app (not diplayed in browser)
Android : http://www.cnet.com/how-to/create-a-shortcut-to-a-web-app-using-chrome-beta-on-android/
IOs : http://www.gottabemobile.com/2012/06/14/how-to-install-the-ios-6-beta-free-no-udid-developer/